01_Data_Setup

Milan Hilde-Jones and Calen P. Ryan

6/30/2021

We have data in dozens of files across decades of time. We need the data in the format we can work with. I'll start bringing things together. A key aspect to this analysis is that it has to be scaleable, in that we will later expand the sample size and need to make it as easy as possible to do so without massive changes to the code.

Load maternal/child data, birthdays, and early growth parameters

Load and inspect 83-86

mbirth2 <-read_dta(here::here("Data/zip_mother_1983_86/mbirth2.dta")) %>% # note: here::here calls the here function
  rename_all(tolower) %>% 
  unite(basebrgy, basewman, sep = "_", col = "basebrgy_basewman")

mlong <-read_dta(here::here("Data/zip_mother_1983_86/mlong.dta")) %>% # note: here::here calls the here function
  rename_all(tolower) %>% 
  unite(basebrgy, basewman, sep = "_", col = "basebrgy_basewman")

Find the variables that relate to growth in this dataset

#subset mbirth data 
growth83_86_birthdata<-mbirth2 %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, outcome, daybirth, mnthbrth, yearbirt, dayintw, mothintw, yearintw, bbweight, weight1, weightak, weightgm, heightcm )
  

#Create variables for birthday and age at first weigh
 growth83_86_birthdata <- growth83_86_birthdata %>%  
  mutate(weightak_kg = (weightak/1900)) %>% 
  mutate(birthdate = make_date(yearbirt + 1900, mnthbrth, daybirth)) %>% 
  mutate(intwdate = make_date(yearintw +1900, mothintw, dayintw)) %>% 
  mutate(age_days_birthweigh = as.numeric(intwdate - birthdate)) %>%
  filter(outcome != "2" | outcome !="3" ) %>% 
  filter(age_days_birthweigh < 30) %>% 
  filter(age_days_birthweigh > 0) %>% 
  filter(weightak > 0) %>% 
  filter(heightcm > 0) 

#zscores for birth data and rename wfaz/hfaz
 
growth83_86_birthdata <- addWGSR(data = growth83_86_birthdata, sex = "sexchild", firstPart= "weightak_kg", secondPart = "age_days_birthweigh", index = "wfa")
## ================================================================================
growth83_86_birthdata <- addWGSR(data = growth83_86_birthdata, sex = "sexchild", firstPart = "heightcm", secondPart = "age_days_birthweigh", index = "hfa")
## ================================================================================
growth83_86_birthdata <- growth83_86_birthdata %>% 
  rename( wfaz_birth = wfaz, hfaz_birth = hfaz)
#subset mlong data and add date of interview
mlong_anthro <-mlong %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, weight, height, yearms, mntham, daymes) %>% 
  mutate(date_inf_meas = lubridate::make_date(year = yearms+1900,
                                              month = mntham,
                                              day = daymes)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(basebrgy_basewman, date_inf_meas)) 


#make a subset for birthday data
birthdates_data <- growth83_86_birthdata %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, birthdate) 
  
#join birthdata and mlong to calculate ages
#unite identifier variables

mlong_anthro_bday <- left_join(birthdates_data, mlong_anthro, by = c("basebrgy_basewman"))
 
mlong_anthro_bday <- mlong_anthro_bday %>% 
   mutate(age_days_infweigh = as.numeric(date_inf_meas - birthdate)) %>% 
   mutate(weight_kg = (weight/1000))

# make the mlong data into wide form, creade new id variables for weight and height 1/12 to reflect first and last infancy measurements

weight_mlong_bday <-mlong_anthro_bday %>%
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, weight_kg, yearms, mntham, daymes, date_inf_meas, age_days_infweigh, birthdate) %>%
  group_by(basebrgy_basewman) %>%
  mutate(id = row_number()) %>%
  filter(id == max(id)) %>%
  arrange(basebrgy_basewman, id) %>% 
  spread(key = id, value = weight_kg, drop = TRUE) %>% 
  rename(wght_12 = "12" )


height_mlong_bday <-mlong_anthro_bday %>%
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, height, date_inf_meas, age_days_infweigh, birthdate) %>%
  group_by(basebrgy_basewman) %>%
  mutate(id = row_number()) %>%
  filter(id == max(id)) %>%
  arrange(basebrgy_basewman, id) %>% 
  spread(key = id, value = height, drop = TRUE) %>% 
  rename(hght_12 = "12" )

z_inf_all_meas<- mlong_anthro_bday %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, height, weight_kg, date_inf_meas, age_days_infweigh, birthdate) 

z_inf_all_meas <- addWGSR(data = z_inf_all_meas, sex = "sexchild", firstPart= "weight_kg", secondPart = "age_days_infweigh", index = "wfa")
## ================================================================================
z_inf_all_meas <- addWGSR(data = z_inf_all_meas, sex = "sexchild", firstPart = "height", secondPart = "age_days_infweigh", index = "hfa")
## ================================================================================
write.csv(z_inf_all_meas,"z_inf_all_meas.csv")

#compute z scores for the 12 infancy measurments 

hfaz_inf_all_meas <-mlong_anthro_bday %>%
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, height, date_inf_meas, age_days_infweigh, birthdate) %>%
  group_by(basebrgy_basewman) %>%
  mutate(id = row_number()) %>%
  arrange(basebrgy_basewman, id) %>% 
  spread(key = id, value = height, drop = TRUE) 

#first height measurment
hfaz_inf_1 <- hfaz_inf_all_meas %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, date_inf_meas, age_days_infweigh, birthdate, "1")

hfaz_inf_1 <- addWGSR(data = hfaz_inf_1, sex = "sexchild", firstPart = "1", secondPart = "age_days_infweigh", index = "hfa") %>% 
  rename(hfaz_1 = hfaz) %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, sexchild, age_days_infweigh, hfaz_1) %>% 
  drop_na()

# Summary: 
# There are many women with codes 10 (Other) or 11 (neither mother nor child present, but that retain values for heightndx etc. for the ICs. The goal will be to filter out those cases where missing values)

Filter out the weird duplicates in 91

child2 %>%
  select(basebrgy_basewman, weghtndx, hightndx, skinndx1, skinndx2, skinndx3, subsndx1, subsndx2, subsndx3, circmndx) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(weghtndx) & !is.na(hightndx)) %>% 
  group_by(basebrgy_basewman) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  filter(n > 1)  
## # A tibble: 0 x 2
## # … with 2 variables: basebrgy_basewman <chr>, n <int>
# Great, this filters out all duplications for child2

child2 <-child2 %>% 
  filter_at(vars(starts_with("skin")), all_vars(.>0)) %>% # filter out people without skinfolds. The guy has -6, which is code for 'disabled, no measurement taken"
  filter_at(vars(starts_with("subs")), all_vars(.>0)) %>%
  na_if(., -9) %>%
  mutate(tricep_mean = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("skin")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  # mean of 3 measurements in mm
  mutate(subscap_mean = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("subs")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  # mean of 3 measurements in mm
  mutate(arm_musc_circ_91 = circmndx*10 - (tricep_mean * 3.14)) %>% # Upper arm muscle circ. (S) in mm: S = c - ( T * 3.14) 
  mutate(arm_musc_area_91 = arm_musc_circ_91^2 / 12.56) %>% # Upper arm muscle area (M) in mm² : M = S² / 12.56
  mutate(bmi_91 = weghtndx/(hightndx/100)^2) %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, weghtndx, hightndx, bmi_91, circmndx, subscap_mean, tricep_mean, arm_musc_area_91) %>% 
  mutate(skinfold_sum = subscap_mean + tricep_mean)

  mutate(bfperc_m_91 = ((14.28*log10(skinfold_sum)-(21.50*log10(hightndx))+ 90.69)),
         bfperc_f_91 = (13.95*log10(skinfold_sum)-(18.09*log10(hightndx))+ 77.17),
         fatmass_m_91 = (( bfperc_m_91 *.01)*weghtndx),
         fatmass_f_91 = (( bfperc_f_91 *.01)*weghtndx),
         fatmass_91 = if_else(sexchild == "1", fatmass_m_91, fatmass_f_91)) %>%
  select(-c(fatmass_f_91, fatmass_m_91)) %>% 
  mutate( fatfree_mass_91 = weghtndx-fatmass_91)

Load and inspect 2002 data

anthdiet <-read_dta(here::here("Data/zip_child_2002/anthdiet.dta")) %>% # note: here::here calls the here function
  rename_all(tolower) %>%

screen_data<-read_dta(here::here("Data/zip_child_2002/screen.dta")) %>% # note: here::here calls the here function
  rename_all(tolower) %>% 
  unite(basebrgy, basewman, sep = "_", col = "basebrgy_basewman")

#subset anthdiet
#calculate bmi
anthdiet <- anthdiet %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, weight, height, tricep1, tricep2, tricep3, subscap1, subscap2, subscap3, waist, hip, armcircm) %>% 
  filter(weight > 0) %>% 
  filter(height > 0) %>% 
  rename(weight_02 = weight, height_02 = height)

anthdiet <-anthdiet %>% 
  filter_at(vars(starts_with("tricep")), all_vars(.>0)) %>% # filter out people without skinfolds. The guy has -6, which is code for 'disabled, no measurement taken"
  filter_at(vars(starts_with("subscap")), all_vars(.>0)) %>%
  na_if(., -9) %>%
  mutate(whr_02 = waist / hip) %>%   
  mutate(tricep_mean = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("tricep")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  # mean of 3 measurements in mm
  mutate(subscap_mean = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("subscap")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  # mean of 3 measurements in mm
  mutate(arm_musc_circ = armcircm*10 - (tricep_mean * 3.14)) %>% # Upper arm muscle circ. (S) in mm: S = c - ( T * 3.14) 
  mutate(arm_musc_area_02 = arm_musc_circ^2 / 12.56) %>% # Upper arm muscle area (M) in mm² : M = S² / 12.56
  mutate(bmi_02 = weight_02/(height_02/100)^2) %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, weight_02, height_02, bmi_02, waist, hip, whr_02, armcircm, subscap_mean, tricep_mean, arm_musc_area_02) %>% 
  mutate(skinfold_sum_02 = subscap_mean + tricep_mean) 

# Calculate the density, fat-free mass, etc.
# Constants from Durnin and Womersley, 1974, (Males, Age 20-29)
# Linear regressionequations for the estimation of body density x 10^3(kg/m^3)
# density = c - m x log skinfold

dw_c_m_02 <-1.1561
dw_m_m_02 <-0.0711

dw_c_f_02 <- 1.1468
dw_m_f_02 <- 0.0740
# bfperc = ((4.95/density )-4.5)*100
# fatmass = (( bfperc *.01)*weight)
# ffm05 = weight-fatmass

 
#subset screen_data
screen_data <- screen_data %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, dayntrvw, yrntrvw, montrvw) %>% 
  mutate(intw_date02 = make_date(yrntrvw, montrvw, dayntrvw))
 
 
#make interview date and find age at interview
screen_data <- left_join(birthdates_data, screen_data, by = c("basebrgy_basewman")) %>% 
  mutate(age_days_02 = as.numeric(intw_date02 - birthdate)) %>% 
  mutate(age_years_02 = age_days_02/365.25) %>% 
  mutate(age_cutoff = if_else(age_years_02 > 19, 19, age_years_02)) %>% 
  mutate(age_cutoff_days = age_cutoff*365.25) %>% 
  filter(age_days_02 > 0)
  
  

growth02_data <- left_join(screen_data, anthdiet, by = c("basebrgy_basewman")) %>% 
  mutate(logfolds = log10(skinfold_sum_02), 
         density_m_02 = dw_c_m_02 - (dw_m_m_02 * logfolds), 
         bfperc_m_02 = ((4.95/density_m_02 )-4.5)*100,
         fatmass_m_02 = (( bfperc_m_02 *.01)*weight_02),
         density_f_02 = dw_c_f_02 - (dw_m_f_02 * logfolds), 
         bfperc_f_02 = ((4.95/density_f_02 )-4.5)*100,
         fatmass_f_02 = (( bfperc_f_02 *.01)*weight_02)) %>% 
  mutate(fatmass_02 = if_else(sexchild == "1", fatmass_m_02, fatmass_f_02)) %>%
  select(-c(fatmass_f_02, fatmass_m_02)) %>% 
  mutate (fatfree_mass_02 = weight_02-fatmass_02)

  

growth02_data <- addWGSR(data = growth02_data, sex = "sexchild", firstPart= "height_02", secondPart = "age_cutoff_days", index = "hfa") %>% 
   rename(hfaz_02 = hfaz)

  rename(weight_05 = weight, height_05 = height, waist_05 = waist, hip_05 = hip, armcircm_05 = armcircm, tricep1_05 = tricep1, tricep2_05 = tricep2, tricep3_05 = tricep3, subscap1_05 = subscap1, subscap2_05 = subscap2, subscap3_05 = subscap3, suprail1_05 = suprail1, suprail2_05 = suprail2, suprail3_05 = suprail3)

  filter_at(vars(starts_with("subscap")), all_vars(.>0)) %>%

  na_if(., -9) %>%
  mutate(whr_05 = waist_05 / hip_05) %>%   
  mutate(tricep_mean = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("tricep")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  # mean of 3 measurements in mm
  mutate(subscap_mean = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("subscap")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  # mean of 3 measurements in mm
  mutate(supra_mean = rowMeans(select(., starts_with("suprail")), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%  # mean of 3 measurements in mm
  mutate(arm_musc_circ = armcircm_05*10 - (tricep_mean * 3.14)) %>% # Upper arm muscle circ. (S) in mm: S = c - ( T * 3.14) 
  mutate(arm_musc_area = arm_musc_circ^2 / 12.56) %>% # Upper arm muscle area (M) in mm² : M = S² / 12.56
  mutate(bmi_05 = weight_05/(height_05/100)^2) %>% 
  select(basebrgy_basewman, age, sex, weight_05, height_05, bmi_05, waist_05, hip_05, whr_05, armcircm_05, subscap_mean, supra_mean, tricep_mean, arm_musc_area) %>% 
  mutate(skinfold_sum = subscap_mean + supra_mean + tricep_mean) 

# Calculate the density, fat-free mass, etc.

# build regression models for birth hfaz
# minimal just clock data and z scores?
# CPR: No minimal models for now. Will run full models and those with interactions

# 12:56:33 From Calen Ryan (he/him/his) to Everyone:
#   EEA ~ delta_growth + pregnancy_status + b_to_2
# 12:56:46 From Calen Ryan (he/him/his) to Everyone:
#   EEA ~ delta_growth + pregnancy_status + b_to_2*delta_growth


grim_height_b_2_f<-lm(AgeAccelGrim ~ hfa_diff_birth_inf12 + 
                        was_preg_no_na, subset(growth_clocks_data, sex == "2"))

grim_height_b_2_m<-lm(AgeAccelGrim ~ hfa_diff_birth_inf12, subset(growth_clocks_data, sex == "1"))

pheno_height_b_2_f <-update(grim_height_b_2_f, AgeAccelPheno ~ .)

pheno_height_b_2_m <-update(grim_height_b_2_m, AgeAccelPheno ~ .-was_preg_no_na)

han_height_b_2_f <-update(grim_height_b_2_f, EEAA ~ .)


han_height_b_2_m <-update(grim_height_b_2_m, EEAA ~ . -was_preg_no_na)


horv_height_b_2_f <-update(grim_height_b_2_f, IEAA ~ .)


horv_height_b_2_m <-update(grim_height_b_2_m, IEAA ~ . -was_preg_no_na)
